messages.content: You are an expert in diagnosing neuropathic pain, using your causal reasoning ability to infer the result of the following question. There are three variables: L Lumbago, L L4 Radikulopati, and L L2 Radikulopati. The order of these variables is randomized. In the context of diagnosing neuropathic pain, consider the causal relationships where A or B will cause discomfort to the collider. This implies that A -> collider or B -> collider.
Identify which variable is the collider in the causal relationship. Only provide the variable name in the following format: 'collider: [variable name]'.
collider: L Lumbago
